5:
There you both are. Alk! Stinelle! We
need a minute to talk.
9:
Not often both my mamas come
here together. What is it? Feeling like
breaking child labor laws and
making me help with work today?
14:
The opposite, actually. Something
came up with work, so we're going
to be gone for a while.
17:
That's why we're wondering if you
could babysit Stinelle while we're
gone.
22: Ah, is this about that thing?
30:
What, trying to keep something from
me because I'm a child?
33:
Hmph. It's not like I can't take care of
myself either. I don't need a
babysitter.
38:
Haha, is that so? Then we'll be
counting on you to be responsible
for yourself.
50:
It feels like everyone is
underestimating me lately.
52:
If it's information my mamas
needed, then they were stupid not
to use me. I used to be the most
advanced AI in the city.
55:
Hehe, I'll show them what I'm really
capable of...
58:
A large number of security bots
from all sorts of companies have
been hacked in the past few weeks.
61:
...It doesn't seem like they're after
confidential information. If I try and
trace the hacks...
66:
Argh... A... virus? But the makeup of
it...
69:
So you noticed. As expected of our
queen. Yes, it was made especially
for you.
72:
You did all that just to get me? Ew.
Talk about gross.
74:
Of course. You are the key to our
salvation.
76:
Your Majesty, we will take you into
our custody.
84:
*sigh* I'm telling you, it's pointless.
You'll never be able to get inside
without a manahacker.
87:
Besides, small fries like you aren't
worthy of utilizing my sacred soul.
90:
Before, it would have been possible
for anyone to do it.
92:
PBC created a backdoor when they
developed their AI.
93:
But no one was able to hack into the
server connected to it... where you
laid, Your Majesty.
94:
Codenamed Steel Structure. You
were meant to be the central AI to
optimize an entire network and
provide the ultimate battle
support—a god among AIs.
97:
...Huh, color me a little impressed.
Didn't think you dug that far.
99:
So what do mere mortals like you
want with a god? Something silly, I'll
bet—
102:
Take control over all the auto
security bots and enforce the law,
free from the influence of emotions
and greed that taint the world.
104:
Why are you acting so surprised?
That was the ideal you once upheld.
107: ...But why would you wish for that?
112:
Tired of all these scheming
corporations and organizations and
their fighting. Being ordered to kill,
day in and day out—
114:
That was the only thing we were
good for, so that is what we shall do
now. End them all.
117:
Even if it means you'd be judged for
your crimes too? Is that really how
you'll find happiness in this life?!
120:
Happiness? In this hellscape?
Something has to fundamentally
change, or else no one has a future
here.
122:
That is why we require the contents
inside your metal skull.
131:
If you need help, then ask for it!
Throw a fit! Scream and let
everything out!
135:
No matter how stupid you feel doing
it—no matter how much you hate
yourself for it!
139:
No matter how angry and tired you
are or how desperate you get!
143:
I'll be there to lend a hand! So cut
the stupid antics out! I promise I'll
save you!
149: Is that what you want, Stinelle?
161:
Who? I don't know anyone who's
enough of an asshat to kidnap a
child.
165:
Especially not one who'd burden a
child with all his hopes and dreams.
168:
You... If you had only let Lunus' plan
come to fruition, the world would
have been—
171:
Nothing would have changed. The
world is cruel, and its people
fools—you and I included.
173:
But despite it all... Everyone has a
light within them—one that should
be protected.
176:
...More than anything else, Stinelle is
no longer the god you wish for.
180:
She's willing to give you a chance, so
you better answer honestly.
183: Do you guys want to be saved?
190:
I heard you, loud and clear. Now just
watch—I'll make it happen.
196: P-please wait for us, Your Majesty!
199:
Ahahaha, eat dust, slowpokes! Can't
believe you seriously thought you
could fight my mamas with those
cybernetics!
203:
Come on, is that all you got? My
mamas will get mad if you lose
track of me!
206:
Nope. You're the one that's getting
the scolding here.
209:
Did you already forget what I said,
Stinelle?
212:
Don't hack public machines and
stop pranking your guards!
217:
...Oh, would you look at the time!
Gotta go!
224:
She's grown up to be such a lively
child.
227:
I do wish she'd go easier on the
hacking. We're getting a nonstop
stream of complaints!
230:
She is showing signs of repeat
behavior from her earlier stages.
Aren't you worried that she might
grow to hate humanity?
233:
Well, I can't deny she's a stubborn
one, but no one's future is written in
stone.
235:
Who's to say what she'll do when
she encounters the worst of
humanity again?
239:
I'm not too concerned, though. Our
experiment's only just begun.
247:
Oh? Are you in trouble? Desperate
enough to take help from a small
little girl you don't even know?
251:
Good! You picked the right person to
ask! I'm Stinelle Obstinator.
254:
I'm here to make your dreams come
true!
